'''Emacs''' denominates [[Article description::a class of powerful, extensible, self-documenting text editors.]] The original implementation still updated today is [[GNU Emacs]], a derivative is [[XEmacs]], which was forked from GNU Emacs in the early 1990s. The latter is not the X version of Emacs but a complete separate program.

